The evidence with the title 'Out-of-wedlock births hit record high - CNN.com ' says Apr 8, 2009  ... Nearly 40 percent of babies born in the United States in 2007 were delivered by unwed mothers , according to data released last month by the National Center For Health Statistics. The 1.7 million out-of-wedlock births, of 4.3 million total births, marked a more than 25 percent jump from five years before. 
